edb / editdisplaybuffer       Opens an 'edit' window for a display buffer line

   Format:
      ;edb <number>           Edits the buffer line <number>
      ;edb                    Edits the most recent buffer line

   Notes:
      The display buffer is Axmud's record of text received from the world and
         displayed in its default tab (see the help for ';displaybuffer').

   User commands:
      edb / editdispbuff / editdisplaybuffer
